{{Infobox person | name = Anna Brożek | image = Anna-Brożek.jpg | image_size = 200px | alt = | caption = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1980|5|11|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Kraków]], Poland | nationality = | education = | alma_mater = [[University of Warsaw]] | occupation = Musician, philosopher | years_active = 2003-present }} Dr. [[habilitation|Hab.]] '''Anna Brożek''' (born May 11, 1980 in [[Kraków]]) is a Polish philosopher and musician.<ref name="CV">{{cite web |url= http://www.anna.brozek.filozofia.uw.edu.pl/AB-Biogram.pdf |title=CV |first=Anna |last=Brozek |work=anna.brozek.filozofia.uw.edu.pl |year=2013 |accessdate=19 June 2013|language=pl}}</ref>
Brożek studied piano at the [[Academy of Music in Kraków]] in 1999-2004, and at the [[Fryderyk Chopin University of Music]] in 2006-2008.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.anna.brozek.filozofia.uw.edu.pl/Zyciorys%20artystyczny.htm |title=Edukacja muzyczna |first= |last= |work=anna.brozek.filozofia.uw.edu.pl |year=2013 |accessdate=19 June 2013|language=pl}}</ref> At the same time she studied philosophy at the [[Pontifical University of John Paul II]] from 1999-2003. Between 2004 and 2006 she completed her PhD studies in philosophy at [[Warsaw University]], gaining her [[habilitation]] in 2008,<ref name="CV"/> and titular [[professorship]] in 2015.
She currently works at the Department of Logical Semiotics at the [[Institute of Philosophy, University of Warsaw]].
