'''Tarja Kallio-Tamminen''' (b. [[Hyvinkää]]) is a [[Finland|Finnish]] researcher of [[philosophy]], academic lecturer and science writer. She has studied [[nuclear physics]] and [[theoretical philosophy]]. Her [[doctoral thesis]] was about the [[interpretation of quantum mechanics]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://notes.helsinki.fi/halvi/tiedotus/vanhatvaitokset.nsf/0/56099f3b502da93ac2256f7b002b61bb?OpenDocument |title=vk 24/04 Kallio-Tamminen Tarja: Filosofia: Quantum Metaphysics. The Role of Human Beings within the Paradigms of Classical and Quantum Physics<!-- Bot generated title --> |access-date=2007-07-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110720182623/http://notes.helsinki.fi/halvi/tiedotus/vanhatvaitokset.nsf/0/56099f3b502da93ac2256f7b002b61bb?OpenDocument |archive-date=2011-07-20 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref> She has written about the conception of [[reality]], foundations of [[quantum physics]] and the [[philosophy of mind]].<ref>[http://www.elisanet.fi/kallio.tamminen/ Dr<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> Kallio-Tamminen is the [[Editor in chief|Chief editor]] of the online philosophical magazine Eko.fi,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kaapeli.fi/eko.fi/main/english.html |title=Eko.fi website |accessdate=2009-10-19 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090409114800/http://www.kaapeli.fi/eko.fi/main/english.html |archivedate=April 9, 2009 }}</ref> which is published by the Green Cultural Association. Kallio-Tamminen was also president of the association from 1990 to 1993.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.physicsfoundations.org/society/kalliotamminen.html |title=Physics Foundations Society biography|accessdate=2009-10-19}}</ref>

==Selected works==
* [http://ethesis.helsinki.fi/julkaisut/hum/filos/vk/kallio-tamminen/ Quantum Metaphysics: The Role of Human Beings within the Paradigms of Classical and Quantum Physics] Academic Dissertation, June 2004. University of Helsinki, Faculty of Arts, Department of Philosophy, Theoretical Philosophy. Oitmäki: Tarja Kallio-Tamminen, 2004. {{ISBN|952-10-1927-1}}
* Kvanttilainen todellisuus: Fysiikka ja filosofia maailmankuvan muokkaajina. Helsinki: Yliopistopaino, 2006. {{ISBN|951-570-625-4}}

